sql:
SELECT service_name
FROM student_support_services
WHERE service_name = 'counseling';

SELECT COUNT(students_graduated) AS number_of_students_graduated
FROM graduation_stats
WHERE year = 2020;

SELECT year 
FROM graduation_stats 
WHERE graduation_rate = (SELECT MAX(graduation_rate) FROM graduation_stats);

external_knowledge:
- High-performing students are those with high cumulative GPAs; 
- Regularly attending students are those with 'present' status in the attendance table; 
- More than half of the total program credits means credits completed greater than 50% of the total program duration in credits (20 * duration_years); 
- Average completed credits percentage is calculated by dividing the average completed credits by the program duration in years and then multiplying by 2 to get the percentage.

sql:
SELECT year, graduation_rate
FROM graduation_stats
ORDER BY year DESC;
